# Free-use positive: a func literal closes over `attrs` (`return
# attrs.Class()`), and the value flows out through a call (`f()`) at a
# sibling fragment. A closure capturing the bag must still trigger the
# implicit-bag synthesis — the free use is inside the literal's body, not
# shadowed by its (empty) parameter list.
